- **Texture and Patterns**: The badge has a smooth, polished surface typical of automotive emblems. There are no visible textures or patterns apart from the reflective finish.

The text "TOYOTA" is prominently displayed in red at the top, followed by "Vandergriff" in black, and "IN KILLEEN" in smaller black text below it. The license plate also includes a black border around the edges. The plate is affixed to the car with standard mounting hardware, and there are no visible signs of damage or unusual wear. The overall appearance is clean and typical of a standard vehicle license plate.

The tail lights of the Chevrolet Malibu in the image are rectangular in shape, with a distinct red color that is consistent across both lights. The texture appears smooth, without any visible patterns or embossments. Each tail light is symmetrically positioned on either side of the rear of the vehicle, flanking the Chevrolet emblem. The size of the tail lights is relatively large compared to the overall dimensions of the car, making them a noticeable feature.

A unique characteristic of these tail lights is their dual-element design, where each light consists of two separate sections: an outer red section and an inner white section. This dual-element design is not common among all vehicles and can be used as a distinguishing feature when comparing this car to others in the same category. Additionally, the taillights have a slight curve at the bottom, adding a subtle aesthetic detail to the otherwise straightforward design.
